743', 'className': 'Compartment', 'schemaClass': 'Compartment'}, {'dbId': 5460, 'displayName': 'mitochondrial matrix', 'accession': '0005759', 'databaseName': 'GO', 'definition': 'The gel-like material, with considerable fine structure, that lies in the matrix space, or lumen, of a mitochondrion. It contains the enzymes of the tricarboxylic acid cycle and, in some organisms, the enzymes concerned with fatty acid oxidation.', 'name': 'mitochondrial matrix', 'url': 'https://www.ebi.ac.uk/QuickGO/term/GO:0005759', 'className': 'Compartment', 'schemaClass': 'Compartment'}, {'dbId': 17906, 'displayName': 'mitochondrial outer membrane', 'accession': '0005741', 'databaseName': 'GO', 'definition': 'The outer, i.e. cytoplasm-facing, lipid bilayer of the mitochondrial envelope.', 'name': 'mitochondrial outer membrane', 'url': 'https://www.ebi.ac.uk/QuickGO/term/GO:0005741', 'className': 'Compartment', 'schemaClass': 'Compartment'}, {'dbId': 7660, 'displayName': 'nucleoplasm', 'accession': '0005654', 'databaseName': 'GO', 'definition': 'That part of the nuclear content other than the chromosomes or the nucleolus.', 'name': 'nucleoplasm', 'url': 'https://www.ebi.ac.uk/QuickGO/term/GO:0005654', 'className': 'Compartment', 'schemaClass': 'Compartment'}, {'dbId': 17951, 'displayName': 'peroxisomal matrix', 'accession': '0005782', 'databaseName': 'GO', 'definition': 'The volume contained within the membranes of a peroxisome; in many cells the matrix contains a crystalloid core largely composed of urate oxidase.', 'name': 'peroxisomal matrix', 'url': 'https://www.ebi.ac.uk/QuickGO/term/GO:0005782', 'className': 'Compartment', 'schemaClass': 'Compartment'}, {'dbId': 17947, 'displayName': 'peroxisomal membrane', 'accession': '0005778', 'databaseName': 'GO', 'definition': 'The lipid bilayer surrounding a peroxisome.', 'name': 'peroxisomal membrane', 'url': 'https://www.ebi.ac.uk/QuickGO/term/GO:0005778', 'className': 'Compartment', 'schemaClass': 'Compartment'}, {'dbId': 876, 'displayN